  "prompt": "What if you order something in a restaurant and they charge you a high price?",
  "response": "If you feel you've been charged an unfairly high price at a restaurant, here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. Check the menu prices first to confirm if the charge matches what was listed.\n\n2. Politely ask the server or manager about the pricing discrepancy.\n\n3. Request an itemized bill to verify each charge.\n\n4. If the price seems genuinely incorrect, discuss it calmly with the staff.\n\n5. If unresolved, you can:\n- Ask to speak with the manager\n- Request a price adjustment\n- Dispute the charge with your credit card company\n- Leave a review explaining the situation\n\n6. As a last resort, you might choose not to return to that restaurant.\n\nThe key is to remain calm, professional, and seek a reasonable resolution.",
